  "author": "Guru Bin",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "Doumbek×2 + Bongos + Frame Drum. 7/8 feel achieved through pattern selection, swing=0.25 for spice-market intimacy. The backroom at 2am, three musicians who have played together for 30 years.",
  "tags": [
    "aether",
    "istanbul",
    "middle-east",
    "doumbek",
    "7-8",
    "transcendental"
  ],
  "tier": "transcendental",
  "guru_bin": {
    "retreat": "OSTINATO — Transcendental Vol 1",
    "retreat_date": "2026-03-19",
    "scripture": [
      "Rumi, from the Masnavi: 'The musicians strike up in your city — and somehow the sound reaches even me, in the dark'",
      "Ottoman proverb: 'The nights of Ramadan belong to the taverns — and the taverns belong to the ney'",
      "Ziya Pasha: 'The soul of the East is in its rhythm — not in its words'"
    ],
    "revelation": "Tempora revealed: swing=0.25 creates the 'Aksak' feel — the Turkish/Balkan limping rhythm that sits between straight and fully swung. At this value, the doumbek pair sounds like it has been playing together since childhood — the slight push and pull is institutionalized rather than random. The 7/8 feel emerges from pattern selection rather than time signature.",
    "god": "Tempora",
    "flock_note": "The Feather noted: two Doumbeks at the same tuning but different articulations (center/open vs. edge/rim) creates the authentic 'dum/tek' voice pair of maqam percussion — the bass stroke and the high stroke that together make the doumbek conversation.",
    "diagnosis": "Midnight Istanbul is muscle memory made audible — the swing value is the 30 years of shared history between musicians who no longer think about what they are playing."
  },
